io.spine.validate

Interface Constraint

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    CustomConstraint
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DistinctConstraint, FieldConstraint, GoesConstraint, IsRequiredConstraint, MaxConstraint, MinConstraint, PatternConstraint, RangeConstraint, RangedConstraint, RequiredConstraint, RequiredFieldConstraint, ValidateConstraint

    @Immutable
public interface Constraint
    A validation rule attributed to a message type.

    A Constraint may cover the values of one or more fields of a message.

      • errorMessage

        java.lang.String errorMessage(FieldContext field)
        Produces an error message for the given field validation context.

        Implementations may choose to ignore the field context or to embed its parts into the error message.

        Parameters:
        field - the validated field

      • accept

        void accept(ConstraintTranslator<?> visitor)
        Accepts the given ConstraintTranslator.
        Implementation Note:
        Constraint and ConstraintTranslator implement the visitor pattern. Implementations should call the appropriate method of ConstraintTranslator.
